# Main/Msg.elm — EARLY

The `Msg` type: every way the Elm runtime can deliver an event
to the update function. Extracted to its own module so that
`Main.Wire`, `Main.Gesture`, `Main.View`, and `Main.elm` can
reference Msg constructors without cyclic imports.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Extracted 2026-04-19 during the Main.elm
  split. Msg was in Main.elm when Main.elm was the whole app;
  now it needs to be importable by the other split modules
  that produce Cmd Msg or wire event handlers.

## Exports

- `Msg(..)` — all constructors exposed (the type is opaque
  only if you want the handler module to be the sole producer,
  which isn't our shape here).

## Constructor groups

**Pointer gestures (drag):**
- `MouseDownOnBoardCard { stack : CardStack, cardIndex : Int } Point Float`
  — stack by content ref; cardIndex is the position within
  the stack, needed by Split.
- `MouseDownOnHandCard Card Point Float`
- `MouseMove Point Float`
- `MouseUp Point Float`
- `BoardRectReceived (Result Browser.Dom.Error Browser.Dom.Element)`
  — Task result for live-drag and replay board-rect lookup.
- `HandCardRectReceived (Result Browser.Dom.Error (Browser.Dom.Element, Time.Posix))`
  — Task result for replay-time DOM lookup of a hand card's
  live viewport rect, paired with `Time.now` so the
  animation's startMs is accurate. Only meaningful when
  `model.replayAnim` is `AwaitingHandRect`.

Wing hover is NOT a Msg. Wing detection is computed in Elm
on each `MouseMove` via `Main.Gesture.floaterOverWing`; no
DOM `mouseenter`/`mouseleave` events are consumed. See
`Main/Gesture.claude` for the "compute, don't delegate"
discipline.

**Button clicks (top-bar + popup):**
- `ClickCompleteTurn`
- `ClickHint`
- `ClickInstantReplay`
- `ClickReplayPauseToggle`
- `PopupOk`

**HTTP responses:**
- `ActionSent (Result Http.Error ())` — fire-and-forget
  action submit; errors ignored today.
- `SessionReceived (Result Http.Error Int)` — new-session
  creation returned a session id.
- `StateRefreshed (Result Http.Error RemoteState)` — /state
  fetch came back.
- `CompleteTurnResponded (Result Http.Error CompleteTurnOutcome)`
  — CompleteTurn /actions POST returned.
- `ActionLogFetched (Result Http.Error ActionLogBundle)` —
  /actions GET came back with log + initial state.

**Timer:**
- `ReplayTick Time.Posix` — 500ms tick while replay is
  active-and-not-paused.

## Dependencies

Imports `Main.State` for the response-shape types
(`RemoteState`, `ActionLogBundle`, `CompleteTurnOutcome`, and
`Point`). Plus `Browser.Dom`, `Http`, `Time`, `Game.Card`,
and `Game.CardStack`.

## What this module deliberately does NOT do

- No handlers. `update` lives in `Main.elm`.
- No Cmd production. HTTP and subscription producers live in
  `Main.Wire` and `Main.elm`'s `subscriptions` function.
